source_code.code:
public class QuickFix
{
  public static void main(String[] args)
  {
    JFrame frame = new JFrame();
    frame.addMouseListener(new MouseAdapter()
    {
      private boolean entered = false;

      @Override
      public void mouseEntered(MouseEvent e)
      {
        this.entered = true;

        Runnable waitRunnable = new Runnable()
        {
          public void run()
          {
            try
            {
              Thread.sleep(150);
            }
            catch(InterruptedException e)
            {}

            if(entered)
            {
              // Do something
            }
          }
        };
        new Thread(waitRunnable).start();
      }

      @Override
      public void mouseExited(MouseEvent e)
      {
        this.entered = false;
      }
    });
  }
}

Bug.WithStack:
When applying the "Qualify with..." Quick-Fix to a field-access within a class nested in a nested class, the outcome produces a syntax error. The following testclass reproduces the problem:

public class QuickFix
{
  public static void main(String[] args)
  {
    JFrame frame = new JFrame();
    frame.addMouseListener(new MouseAdapter()
    {
      private boolean entered = false;

      @Override
      public void mouseEntered(MouseEvent e)
      {
        this.entered = true;

        Runnable waitRunnable = new Runnable()
        {
          public void run()
          {
            try
            {
              Thread.sleep(150);
            }
            catch(InterruptedException e)
            {}

            if(entered)
            {
              // Do something
            }
          }
        };
        new Thread(waitRunnable).start();
      }

      @Override
      public void mouseExited(MouseEvent e)
      {
        this.entered = false;
      }
    });
  }
}

Trying to Quick-Fix the "if(entered)" statement, the result is "MouseAdapter.this.entered", which results in a compilation problem. 
I don't know what would be the correct way to access this field qualified, so let me please know when resolving this issue ;)
I have to disappoint you, it's not possible.

Btw, nice code;-) Be careful with race conditions...

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 115277 ***

