    x();
    y();
z();

And it wasn't immediately obvious to me that there was a mistake here: statement "y()" should have been outdented to indicate it wasn't going to be executed inside the for loop.

It would be nice if the compiler could issue a warning or error in these cases where the human eye reads a statement as part of the previous loop or condition.


